claim.claim-text:
1. A system for simulating one or more tasks using virtual reality, the system comprising:
a portable motion capture system at a location positioned to track movements of one or more users and to record full-body motion capture data for the one or more users performing one or more tasks;
wherein the portable motion capture system comprising:
a motion capture bodysuit having markers at predetermined locations;
a plurality of cameras positioned to record images that capture movements of the one or more users wearing the motion capture bodysuit; and
one or more computers to digitally record locations of the markers associated with the bodysuit, responsive to the recorded images from the plurality of cameras;

a remote camera at a location remote from the users that records an image of the location;
a virtual reality simulator being positioned to receive the motion capture data and capable of animating one or more avatars within the three-dimensional virtual reality simulation, responsive to the motion capture data of the motion capture systems and image recorded by the remote camera; and
an immersive observation system to display the virtual reality simulation, including the one or more animated avatars, as a three-dimensional image using one or more head mounted displays so that each of the one or more head mounted displays can provide a different perspective of the virtual reality simulation and that selectively switches between the virtual reality simulation and the image recorded by the remote camera.

10. A computer program product, stored in one or more non-transitory tangible computer readable media and readable by a computer so that the computer program product operates to perform the following instructions when read by the computer:
recording full-body motion capture data for a set of one or more users performing one or more tasks by a portable motion capture system;
recording an image at a location remote to the users with a remote camera to obtain a telepresence view
wherein the portable motion capture systems comprises:
a motion capture bodysuit having markers at predetermined locations;
a plurality of cameras positioned to record images that capture movements of the one or more users wearing the motion capture bodysuit; and
one or more computers to digitally record locations of the markers associated with the bodysuit, responsive to the recorded images from the plurality of cameras;

animating one or more avatars within a the virtual reality simulation by a virtual reality simulator responsive to motion capture data for the one or more users of the first and second motion capture systems so that each of the one or more users corresponds to one of the one or more avatars;
displaying the virtual reality simulation, including the one or more animated avatars, as a three-dimensional image using one or more head mounted displays so that each of the one or more head mounted displays can provide a different perspective of the virtual reality simulation and selectively displaying the telepresence view.

12. A method of simulating a task, the method comprising:
recording full-body motion capture data for a set of one or more users performing one or more tasks by a portable motion capture system;
recording a telepresence view from a location remote to the users
wherein the portable motion capture systems each comprises:
a motion capture bodysuit having markers at predetermined locations;
a plurality of cameras positioned to record images that capture movements of the one or more users wearing the motion capture bodysuit; and
one or more computers to digitally record locations of the markers associated with the bodysuit, responsive to the recorded images from the plurality of cameras;

animating one or more avatars within a the virtual reality simulation by a virtual reality simulator responsive to motion capture data for the one or more users of the motion capture systems so that each of the one or more users corresponds to one of the one or more avatars;
displaying the virtual reality simulation, including the one or more animated avatars, as a three-dimensional image using one or more head mounted displays so that each of the one or more head mounted displays can provide a different perspective of the virtual reality simulation; and
selectively displaying the telepresence view to validate the simulation.
